From a55a3b5d0ff1a0a4eff4db65bd0c0f3a6506af80 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 22:33:01 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] WifiHAl: Fix fatal use-after-free causing infinite POLLNVAL
 loop

On older bcmdhd drivers (like Exynos3475), the `vendor` netlink
multicast group is not supported. During `wifi_pre_initialize()`,
`wifi_add_membership(handle, "vendor")` fails, which triggers the
error path where the HAL frees the netlink sockets and the
global `halInfo` struct.

However, the code failed to set the global `halInfo` pointer to
`NULL` after calling `free(halInfo)`. When the framework subsequently
called `wifi_initialize()`, the HAL saw `halInfo != NULL` (as a
dangling pointer) and bypassed initialization, assuming it succeeded.
The HAL then started the `wifi_event_loop` thread, which repeatedly
called `poll()` on the now-closed netlink socket file descriptor.
This resulted in `poll()` infinitely returning the `POLLNVAL` (0x20)
error flag, spewing thousands of "Unknown event - 20, 0" logs per
second until `android.hardware.wifi@1.0-service` aborted.

This patch fixes the issue by:
1. Moving the `vendor` multicast group registration outside of the
   fatal error block, making it optional so the HAL can continue
   initializing even if the driver lacks support for it.
2. Explicitly setting `halInfo = NULL;` after `free(halInfo)` in all
   error paths to permanently eradicate the use-after-free vulnerability.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Change-Id: I183a67339e71b48d5f144277dabce696a67b8743
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 bcmdhd/wifi_hal/wifi_hal.cpp | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bcmdhd/wifi_hal/wifi_hal.cpp b/bcmdhd/wifi_hal/wifi_hal.cpp
index 258725c..eb3f232 100755
--- a/bcmdhd/wifi_hal/wifi_hal.cpp
+++ b/bcmdhd/wifi_hal/wifi_hal.cpp
@@ -355,20 +355,22 @@ wifi_error wifi_pre_initialize(void)
         nl_socket_free(event_sock);
         pthread_mutex_destroy(&halInfo->cb_lock);
         free(halInfo);
+        halInfo = NULL;
         return WIFI_ERROR_NOT_AVAILABLE;
     }
 
     if ((wifi_add_membership(handle, "scan") < 0) ||
             (wifi_add_membership(handle, "mlme")  < 0) ||
-            (wifi_add_membership(handle, "regulatory") < 0) ||
-            (wifi_add_membership(handle, "vendor") < 0)) {
+            (wifi_add_membership(handle, "regulatory") < 0)) {
         ALOGE("Add membership failed");
         nl_socket_free(cmd_sock);
         nl_socket_free(event_sock);
         pthread_mutex_destroy(&halInfo->cb_lock);
         free(halInfo);
+        halInfo = NULL;
         return WIFI_ERROR_NOT_AVAILABLE;
     }
+    wifi_add_membership(handle, "vendor");
 
     ALOGI("Initialized Wifi HAL Successfully; vendor cmd = %d", NL80211_CMD_VENDOR);
     wlan0Handle = wifi_get_wlan_interface((wifi_handle)halInfo, ifaceHandles, numIfaceHandles);
